  "texts": [
    "[122] addressed these challenges by utilizing cyberGIS-Jupyter for the city of Chicago, Illinois, enabling a seamless integration of advanced cyberinfrastructure, Geospatial Information Systems, and spatial analysis.",
    "[125] employed geospatial data analytics to assess UHI variations in New York City, aiding the city's \"cool neighborhoods\" program to target areas most in need of cooling interventions.",
    "[126] combined with short turnaround times satel-lite imagery, Earth observation data, and ML algorithms based on the Google Cloud computing platform.",
    "• ML techniques: While traditional statistical methods, such as those based on the Pearson coefficient to identify relationships, are still employed for UHI analysis, an increasing number of scientists are turning to ML methods for processing and forecasting UHI, as noted in [124].",
    "Fueled by Big Data, ML techniques can contribute to predicting UHI patterns with high accuracy."
  ]
